Titan Tumbles Most in Four Months in Mumbai on Valuation Concern

-- B y   M a l a v i k a   S h a r m a
-- 
2011-06-22T11:27:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/titan-tumbles-most-in-four-months-in-mumbai-on-valuation-concern.html
Titan Industries Ltd. (TTAN)  fell the most
in more than four months in Mumbai on concern a rally that’s
made the stock the second-best performer on the Bombay Stock
Exchange 200 Index this year has overvalued earnings prospects.  Titan,  India ’s biggest maker of watches, fell 6.3 percent
to 4,292.5 rupees at the 3:30 p.m. close, the steepest decline
since Feb. 8, and the worst performer on the index. More than
1.4 million shares changed hands, or four times the three-month
daily average, data compiled by Bloomberg show.  The company’s shares, which have doubled in the 12 months
through yesterday, trade at 32 times estimated profit. The BSE
200 is at a multiple of 13.5 times. The benchmark Bombay Stock
Exchange Sensitive Index trades at 14.2 times.  Titan “is an extremely expensive stock,” Manoj Menon, a
Mumbai-based analyst with Kotak Institutional Equities said in a
telephone interview. The shares have reached levels that “are
clearly not sustainable.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
